{#
  user_message.jinja — Spool-authored template for US-CMP-005.

  Rendered per drive against analytics output. See src/server/analytics/
  basic.py (DriveStatistics) and advanced.py (AnomalyResult, TrendResult,
  CorrelationResult) for the source shapes. Fields below match the contract
  Marcus outlined in 2026-04-16-from-marcus-ai-prompt-templates.md.

  Render contract (fields the renderer must pass):
    drive_id            int
    drive_start         ISO-8601 string (UTC)
    duration_seconds    int
    row_count           int
    statistics          list of { parameter, min, max, avg, std, sample_count }
    anomalies           list of { parameter, sigma, direction, historical_avg }
    trend               list of { parameter, direction, percent_delta, significance }
    correlations        list of { param_a, param_b, coefficient }
    prior_drives_count  int

  All lists may be empty. Jinja handles empty lists explicitly so the prompt
  stays clean and Ollama is not asked to reason about an empty section.
#}
## Drive under analysis

- Drive ID: {{ drive_id }}
- Started: {{ drive_start }}
- Duration: {{ duration_seconds }} seconds
- Samples collected: {{ row_count }}
- Prior drives in baseline: {{ prior_drives_count }}

{% if prior_drives_count < 5 -%}
**Baseline note**: fewer than 5 prior drives are in the history. Trend and
anomaly data are early-stage. Weight your recommendations accordingly and
lean toward "observe and revisit" rather than "act now" unless a safety
threshold is clearly crossed.
{%- endif %}

## Per-parameter statistics (this drive)

{% if statistics -%}
| Parameter | Min | Max | Avg | Std Dev | Samples |
|-----------|-----|-----|-----|---------|---------|
{% for s in statistics -%}
| {{ s.parameter }} | {{ "%.2f"|format(s.min) }} | {{ "%.2f"|format(s.max) }} | {{ "%.2f"|format(s.avg) }} | {{ "%.2f"|format(s.std) }} | {{ s.sample_count }} |
{% endfor %}
{%- else -%}
_No per-parameter statistics were computed for this drive._
{%- endif %}

## Anomalies (≥ 2σ from historical baseline)

{% if anomalies -%}
| Parameter | Sigma | Direction | Historical Avg |
|-----------|-------|-----------|----------------|
{% for a in anomalies -%}
| {{ a.parameter }} | {{ "%.2f"|format(a.sigma) }} | {{ a.direction }} | {{ "%.2f"|format(a.historical_avg) }} |
{% endfor %}

Anomalies ≥ 3σ are high-confidence investigations. Anomalies 2σ–3σ are
watch items — real enough to mention, not alone enough to alarm.
{%- else -%}
_No anomalies flagged this drive._
{%- endif %}

## Rolling trends

{% if trend -%}
| Parameter | Direction | % Change | Significance |
|-----------|-----------|----------|--------------|
{% for t in trend -%}
| {{ t.parameter }} | {{ t.direction }} | {{ "%+.1f"|format(t.percent_delta) }}% | {{ t.significance }} |
{% endfor %}
{%- else -%}
_No trend data available — need more drives in the history._
{%- endif %}

## Cross-parameter correlations

{% if correlations -%}
{% for c in correlations -%}
- {{ c.param_a }} ↔ {{ c.param_b }}: Pearson r = {{ "%+.2f"|format(c.coefficient) }}
{% endfor %}

|r| > 0.7 = strong. 0.4–0.7 = moderate. Below 0.4 is noise; ignore.
{%- else -%}
_No significant correlations detected._
{%- endif %}

## Your task

Review the data above and produce up to 5 recommendations as a JSON array,
per the output format specified in your instructions.

Before including each recommendation, ask yourself:
1. Can I point to a specific number or row above that triggered this?
2. Is this recommendation within the hardware envelope for this car?
3. Would this advice apply to ANY car, or specifically to the data I just saw?

If the answer to (1) is no, drop it. If (2) is no, drop it. If (3) is "any
car" — it is noise, drop it.

Return the JSON array now. No prose, no preamble, no markdown fences.
